# Admin design system

When editing admin pages or components, follow [docs/DESIGN_ADMIN.md](../../docs/DESIGN_ADMIN.md).

## Palette (Stripe)

- **Primary** `#0A2540` — headlines, body text
- **Secondary** `#425466` — labels, captions, borders
- **Tertiary** `#635BFF` — **sole interaction accent** (primary buttons only)
- **Neutral** `#F6F9FC` — page canvas
- **Surface** `#FFFFFF` — cards, sidebar, inputs

## Rules

- Use admin tokens via `.vsport-admin` CSS vars and components under `resources/js/components/admin/`.
- Do **not** import from `@/components/storefront/*`.
- Do **not** use storefront classes or hardcode `slate-*` — use `text-admin-secondary`, `border-admin`, `var(--admin-primary)`, etc.
- **One tertiary CTA per screen** — other actions: `secondary`, `ghost`, or text links.
- **No gradients** — flat surfaces only.
- Light sidebar (surface/neutral), not dark chrome.
- Card radius 16px (`rounded-admin-lg`); button radius 10px (`rounded-admin-md`).

## Layout width (`max-w-*`)

- **Default: full width.** Admin page content lives in the `p-6` shell — do not wrap forms, tables, or multi-field sections in `max-w-*`.
- **Use `max-w-*` only when the UI is intentionally narrow:** compact filter bars, single-purpose create forms that match an existing page pattern (e.g. `max-w-2xl` on product create), or `truncate` on table cells (`max-w-xs` + ellipsis). For modals, use the shared `DialogContent` width (`w-[min(calc(100vw-2rem),32rem)]`) — do not add extra `max-w-md` / `sm:max-w-*` unless a smaller modal is explicitly required.
- **Never** put `max-w-*` on containers that hold grids, image previews, badges + action buttons, or rich campaign/product data — it squeezes content and breaks layout.
- Prefer `grid` / `flex-wrap` / `min-w-0` for responsive layout instead of capping page width.

Preview: `/admin/preview/design-system` (admin auth required).
